<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hoshi</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-06-10"><hi rend="italic">June 10,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 41.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Reserving consideration of the statements
                            and representations therein contained, I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt of your note of the 4th instant, in reply to that of this
                            Department of the 2d instant, respecting the recent legislation of Japan
                            granting a bounty for the exportation of silk by Japanese subjects.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>